SUMMARY:Birds at the Battlefield (Currie)
DESCRIPTION:Join NCWF and Cape Fear Audubon for a bird walk at Moores Creek National Battlefield. Part of the NC birding trail\, this historic site encompasses blackwater cypress swamp and restored longleaf pine savanna\, with over 100 species of birds on record. Late March is the perfect time to catch migratory songbirds on their way back to their breeding grounds. \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/birds-at-the-battlefield-currie/
CATEGORIES:Featured
END:VEVENT
